Richard was born on [18 October
1862](/images/braginton_richard_descendants.pdf) (also
[FamilySearch
record](https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2N8V-TNL)
to [Edmund Allen Johns and Clara Louisa Braginton]({{< relref
"johns-braginton.pdc" >}}).

See the [Richard Braginton Johns Ancestry.com
page](https://www.ancestry.com.au/genealogy/records/richard-braginton-johns-24-qy2hdl)
for more suggestions.

He married [Mary
Sherwin](https://www.freebmd.org.uk/cgi/information.pl?cite=qFnFz44Z8kjzz9N%2FyRFivw&scan=1)
in 1889.  Mary [probably died in
1898](https://www.freebmd.org.uk/cgi/information.pl?cite=wYyAzYWxxrwwwE3Nsy9lRA&scan=1).

In 1902 he [married Georgiana Lucy
Deacon](https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QLH8-DS6N)

See this [Wikitree page for
Georgiana](https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Wolfe-7010).

His household in Plymouth in the [1911
census](https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:XW9K-NSV)
is his wife, two children (see below) and a cook, two servants,
a governess, a chauffeur and a stable boy.

His children from the 1911 census were:

* Richard Allen Pendomer (?) Johns, age 18
* George Edward (?) Wolfe Johns, age 5

Richard Allen Pendarves Johns was born in Plymouth [around September
1892](https://www.freebmd.org.uk/cgi/information.pl?cite=6jQAQQG%2BeFY%2BEJcwzNlOZw&scan=1)

He was a lieutenant in the 20th Hussars in the 1914-18 war. His [National
Archives service
record](https://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/details/r/D8278047) has him:

* With next of kin R. B. Johns, of Plymouth, Father.
* Reported missing in France on 23 May 1917.
* Unofficially reported wounded and prisoner of war in 4 June 1917.
* Noted as "Dead" but this crossed out in one of two places.
* Repatriated prisoner of war on 5 January 1919.

In fact, he died in India, in 1922, aged around 29. From the free search for
"Richard Allen Johns" in the "Western Morning News" at
<https://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk>:

> LATE MR. R. A. P. JOHNS
>
>... LATE MR. R. A. P. JOHNS. PLYMOUTH CORONER'S BEREAVEMENT.
regret to announce tM~deatb India the sou of Mr. R. B. Johns,
the coroner for Plymouth. •Mr. Richard Allen Pendarves Johns,
aged was shooting Lake Adra last Thursday, and entering the ...

[Richard Allen's
beneficiary](https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QPLD-B1Y6)
was his father.

