Georgiana died on holiday with Richard in Italy, in 1937. The record appears in
the free search for "Georgiana Johns" in the "Western Morning News" at
<https://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk>, but the full version quoted here
is from [this Wikitree page](https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Wolfe-7010):

> DIED IN ITALY
>
> Wife of a Plymouth Magistrate. Many friends in Plymouth will
learn with regret of the death abroad of Mrs Georgiana Lucy
Johns, wife of Mr. R. B. Johns solicitor and city magistrate,
of Plymouth, who had resided at The Terrace, The Hoe. Mrs Johns
had been on a holiday visit to Italy with Mr. Johns, and death
occurred at Menaggio, Italy, after short illness.

[Her probate](/images/georgiana_lucy_johns_probate_1937.png) benefits her
husband, and Flora Georgiana Deacon, the daughter from her first marriage (see
Wikitree link above).

Richard himself [died on 22 July
1952](/images/richard_braginton_johns_probate_1952.png), leaving his £82940 to
William Ernest Blakeney solicitor, and his step-daughter Flora Georgiana
Deacon.
